reviewText: My wife and I watched this when she was struggling with terminal cancer. Although quite familiar with the Psalm prior, it attained a different relevance during those difficult times. Recollections are instantaneous when only viewing the cover amongst the other various titles. I hope it has served others well.

reviewText: I have to buy a new one, it will be the fourth that I have bought because it is so good I keep giving them away.  Very soft spoken and very quite soft music babbling brooks in the background as the author narrates and teaches about Psalm 23 from the Holy Land. Chemo patients need quite and soft comfortable things to listen to, this is it.
